istian church, he explains, was one not of obliteration but of widening embrace and assimilation. This fascinating book also includes new material on the Christian persecution of pagans over the centuries through methods that ranged from fines to crucifixion; the mixture of motives in conversion; the stubbornness of pagan resistance; the difficulty of satisfying the demands and expectations of new converts; and the degree of assimilation of Christianity to paganism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aChristianity and culturexHistoryyEarly church, ca. 30-600. 0aChurch historyyPrimitive and early church, ca. 30-600. 0aEvangelistic workxHistoryyEarly church, ca. 30-600. 0aPaganismxRelationsxChristianity. 7aRELIGION / Comparative Religion.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030007148140uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030014754440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300147544423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300147544/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY